<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <%- include('head', { title: 'Redacted Bodies | Noir Mak', description: 'Redacted Bodies — a generative art project by Noir Mak exploring queer identity, censorship, surveillance, and digital embodiment through a custom LoRA model trained on FLUX.' }) %>

    <body>

        <%- include('header') %>

        <main>

            <!-- COLLECTION BANNER -->
            <section id="collection-banner">
                <div class="container">
                    <p class="featured-label">Generative Art</p>
                    <h1 class="hero-title">Redacted Bodies</h1>
                    <p class="hero-tagline">A custom-trained LoRA model exploring queer identity, censorship, surveillance, and digital embodiment</p>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END COLLECTION BANNER -->

            <!-- PROCESS -->
            <section id="collection-process">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="about-card">
                        <p class="featured-label">The Process</p>
                        <h2>Building the Model</h2>
                        <p class="about-text">Redacted Bodies is built around a custom LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) model, trained on top of FLUX and developed in ComfyUI. Rather than hand-drawing or photographing each piece, the imagery emerges from a model fine-tuned on a hand-curated dataset — every image in that dataset chosen deliberately to carry the project's themes of visibility, redaction, and the body under surveillance.</p>
                        <p class="about-text">The dataset design and prompt engineering are as much the artwork as the generated output: what gets shown, what gets withheld, and what the model learns to associate with "redaction" are all authorial choices. The result is a generative pipeline that produces new, unrepeatable variations while staying tethered to a consistent visual and conceptual language.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END PROCESS -->

            <!-- GALLERY -->
            <section id="collection-gallery">
                <div class="container">
                    <p class="featured-label text-center">Generated Work</p>
                    <h2 class="section-title text-center">Gallery</h2>
                    <div class="row g-4 mt-2">
                        <% const galleryAccents = ['card-accent-1', 'card-accent-2', 'card-accent-3', 'card-accent-4']; %>
                        <% const numerals = ['I', 'II', 'III', 'IV', 'V', 'VI', 'VII', 'VIII', 'IX']; %>
                        <% for (let i = 1; i <= 9; i++) { %>
                        <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 project-card-wrapper" style="--card-delay: <%= (i - 1) * 0.08 %>s">
                            <div class="project-card gallery-card <%= galleryAccents[(i - 1) % 4] %>">
                                <img src="/images/redacted-bodies-gen-<%= String(i).padStart(2, '0') %>.png" alt="Redacted Bodies — generated piece <%= numerals[i - 1] %>" class="gallery-img" width="512" height="512" loading="lazy">
                                <p class="gallery-caption">Redacted Bodies — <%= numerals[i - 1] %></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <% } %>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section><!-- END GALLERY -->

        </main><!-- END MAIN -->

        <%- include('footer') %>

    </body>

</html>
